            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Blue 
Yonder 
SPM</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-4D225FD0-0B3A-45A9-8199-75EE0EA66F89" signavio:alignment="left">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioDictionaryLink propertyId="name">
               <signavio:dictionaryLink>/glossary/04b83b1aa5da43179b6ed26475955f26</signavio:dictionaryLink>
            </signavio:signavioDictionaryLink>
            <signavio:signavioType dataObjectType="IT-System"/>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bgcolor" metaValue="#e1e1e1"/>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel align="right" bottom="false" left="true" ref="text_name" right="false" top="false" valign="middle" x="-7.0" y="29.0"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Blue 
Yonder 
SPM</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-E86E0408-F57D-4FBB-AACF-86AED368D92F" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Supply Allocation Report is reviewed based on customer segmentation/ prioritization logic</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-E6881734-E35A-47B5-8027-0499D58CB58B" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>There will be a manual escalation process (outside of nightly reprocessing) where a CBA can raise only critical orders (not everything) Scope of escalaltion file: Customer orders confirmed &amp; unconfirmed within the promise horizon Products on and off allocation Requires stronger justification than CMAD &gt;RMAD Excludes RTF and supply escalations (AR - Supply health escalations process TBD )</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <group categoryValueRef="sid-32e2ad72-22cf-4139-8283-85c78904e30a" id="sid-CAFC35B9-3635-4281-9FD2-4C34ED0F2C0C">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
      </group>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-01B4C3B1-F992-4264-90F7-5B9C9BFEA474" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="true" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="48.0" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="true" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="48.0" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform Process Steward: Michel Al, Shawi &lt;michel.al.shawi@intel.com&gt;, and BPM Champion: Rebeca, Meza Redondo &lt;rebeca.meza.redondo@intel.com&gt; of any changes that occur within the flow from now onwards so that changes can be accurately reflected within BIC</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
